-- Forint Snaps Three-Day Gain as Moody's Puts Hungary Debt Ratings on Review
-- Piotr Skolimowski
-- 2010-07-23T07:33:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/forint-snaps-three-day-gain-as-moody-s-puts-hungary-debt-ratings-on-review.html

          
          
             The forint dropped against the euro
for the first time in four days after Moody’s Investors Service
placed Hungary’s Baa1 local and foreign-currency government bond
ratings on review for possible downgrade.  
 The forint dropped 0.4 percent to 285.65 per euro as of
9:27 a.m. in Budapest. The BUX Index slid 0.7 percent.  
